In Aspire, how to we force services to be internal only and not exposes externally ?

I don't want "microservice1" and "mocirsoervice2" endpoints exposed externally to the internet, just my apigateway API:

(I'm also deploying to Kubernetes using Aspir8......)

var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Add microservices
var microservice1 = builder.AddProject<Projects.microservice1>("microservice1");
var microservice2 = builder.AddProject<Projects.microservice2>("microservice2");

// Configure API Gateway
builder.AddProject<Projects.apigateway>("apigateway")
    .WithReference(microservice1)
    .WithReference(microservice2);
    //.WithExternalHttpEndpoints();
    //.WithReplicas(3);

builder.Build().Run();

@plppp2001 

> In Aspire, how to we force services to be internal only and not exposes externally ?

Unless you mark the modelled endpoints as external, e.g. by calling `WithExternalHttpEndpoints()`, they're "internal" from a modelling point-of-view. Enforcing that is completely up to your deployment mechanism though. For example, `azd` ensures that only endpoints marked as external are setup for external ingress on Azure Container Apps.

