You just inspired me to try combining `WithContainerFiles` and `WithVolume` and that looks to give us exactly the behavior you're looking for. I modified your example like this and the startup script ran successfully. I even attached the volumes to another container with `--volumes-from` and confirmed the permissions and created files/folders were all present:

```C#
container
    .WithVolume("/mnt/something")
    .WithVolume("/tmp/something")
    .WithVolume("/home/app/mount")
    .WithContainerFiles("/mnt", [
        new ContainerDirectory
        {
            Name = "something",
            Owner = 1654,
            Group = 1654,
        },
    ])
    .WithContainerFiles("/tmp", [
        new ContainerDirectory
        {
            Name = "something",
            Owner = 1654,
            Group = 1654,
        },
    ])
    .WithContainerFiles("/home/app", [
        new ContainerDirectory
        {
            Name = "mount",
            Owner = 1654,
            Group = 1654,
        },
    ]);
```

